<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 24 at 10:07PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>A band of light to moderate snow showers moving across Long Island
and southern Connecticut should bring at least a coating of
accumulation, and as much as an inch across portions of interior
southern Connecticut. Slippery travel is possible, especially on
less traveled and untreated roadways. Motorists should use extra
caution if driving tonight. The light snow should end before
midnight in most places, but could linger until about 1 AM east of
the Connecticut River and across the forks of Long Island.</description>
